Aggregatable and Non-Aggregatable Metrics

When creating multidimensional metrics in Data Cloud, you can’t aggregate or collapse some Calculated Insights functions or metrics for one or more dimensions. These measures are called non-aggregatable metrics. Examples of non-aggregatable functions include Rank, NTILE, and Case.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience

When querying a non-aggregatable metric, provide all the dimensions that you want to use when creating the metrics.

EXAMPLE You create a Calculated Insights measure called “Rank customers by total spend by product category and location.” Because this measure involves a Rank function, you can’t aggregate or collapse it on an arbitrary dimension. When querying the metrics, you must provide values for all the dimensions. In this case, your query can look like this:

Find customers using these criteria: Top 100 customers by spending by “Product Category == Furniture” and “Location = Bellevue”. You can see if a function is non-aggregatable in the object home screen of the Calculated Insights.

EXAMPLE The rank is calculated against spend and channel. You can't aggregate the rank values further if you reduce the dimension.

SELECT
 ssot__SalesOrder__dlm.ssot__SalesChannelId__c AS channel__c,
RANK() OVER (ORDER BY SUM(ssot__SalesOrder__dlm.ssot__GrandTotalAmount__c) asc) AS spend_rank__c,
UnifiedIndividual__dlm.ssot__Id__c AS unified_individual__c
FROM
ssot__SalesOrder__dlm
JOIN IndividualIdentityLink__dlm ON (ssot__SalesOrder__dlm.ssot__SoldToCustomerId__c = IndividualIdentityLink__dlm.SourceRecordId__c)
JOIN UnifiedIndividual__dlm ON (IndividualIdentityLink__dlm.UnifiedRecordId__c = UnifiedIndividual__dlm.ssot__Id__c)
GROUP BY
unified_individual__c,
channel__c
